Winner-winner sure-fire chicken dinner—this meal's got comfy and cozy date-night-in vibes to spare! Chicken cutlets are seared to a deep brown with a savory seasoning blend, then smothered in a rich, creamy shallot pan sauce (with plenty of sauce left to give some love to the fluffy, garlicky mashed potatoes). Roasted prosciutto-wrapped asparagus bundles sprinkled with lemon zest add a luxurious touch to your table.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

== Prep ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces (for smoother mashed potatoes, peel first).

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @Asparagus{6%ounce}.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @Shallot{1}.

Zest and quarter @Lemon{1}.

== Potatoes ==

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches.

Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> Cover with a lid to bring to a boil more quickly.

Reserve 1 cup potato cooking liquid (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings); drain and return potatoes to pot. Keep covered off heat until ready to mash.

== Prosciutto-Wrapped Asparagus ==

Gather asparagus into four even bundles (eight bundles for 4 servings) on a clean work surface.

Starting 1 inch from the bottom of the spears, roll up each bundle of asparagus in a slice of @Prosciutto{2%ounce}, so that the prosciutto covers as much length as possible.

> Tug the prosciutto a little as you wrap to keep it tight around the asparagus.

Place wrapped asparagus on a #baking sheet{}; roast on top rack for ~{10%minutes}, then flip and roast until crispy all over, ~{2-4%minutes} more.

Sprinkle @Lemon{1}(zested) and a squeeze of lemon juice over asparagus.

== Chicken ==

Meanwhile, pat @Chicken Cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season generously all over with @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @Salt{} and @Pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

> Lower heat and cover if chicken begins to brown too quickly.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}. Wipe out pan.

== Shallot Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium heat. Add shallot; cook until softened and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in @Chicken Stock Concentrate{2} and 1/3 cup water (2/3 cup for 4 servings). Bring to a simmer, then reduce heat to low. Cook until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in half the @Sour Cream{3%tablespoon} and @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4).

== Mashed Potatoes ==

To pot with drained potatoes, add @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining sour cream, and @Butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4 servings). Mash with a #potato masher{} over medium-low heat until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Taste and season generously with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide prosciutto-wrapped asparagus and mashed potatoes between plates. Place chicken atop potatoes and drizzle with creamy shallot sauce. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges.